dataIdInfo.idPurp: The data were developed as an input to a series of province-level maps, U695, U696, and U697. HIU prepared these maps to support the planning of prevention of mother-to-child transmission of HIV programs (PMTCT) in three priority provinces in The Democratic Republic of the Congo.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
The shapefile of DRC health zones was obtained from the original author, Louis Ilunga of WHO. The shapefile was made for DRC MOH. HIU improved the shapefile by eliminating splinters and many other errors in the original vectors.

The lack of health zone-level population data led us to calculate zonal statistics from Landscan raster data. The data are attached as columns in the table.

ISPOP - Landscan 2011

http://www.ornl.gov/sci/landscan/
